    "body": "\r\n\r\n\r\n## Purpose\r\nExternal memset is introduced in #41444 but only when `need_cooperative` is true. `need_cooperative` only trigger when `max_seq_len` is greater than a certain threshold. And this means that the trigger will never fire at cuda graph capture time. \r\n\r\nThis PR remove `need_cooperative` statement so that the memset kernel is always trigger at capture time. \r\n\r\n## Test Plan\r\ngsm8k v4-pro DEP4 on B300 MTP2\r\n\r\n## Test Result\r\n```\r\n|Tasks|Version|     Filter     |n-shot|  Metric   |   |Value |   |Stderr|\r\n|-----|------:|----------------|-----:|-----------|---|-----:|---|-----:|\r\n|gsm8k|      3|flexible-extract|     5|exact_match|↑  |0.9522|±  |0.0059|\r\n|     |       |strict-match    |     5|exact_match|↑  |0.9522|±  |0.0059|\r\n```\r\n\r\nSpeedbench 8k/1k result\r\n```\r\n================= Serving Benchmark Result =================\r\nSuccessful requests:                     10        \r\nFailed requests:                         0         \r\nMaximum request concurrency:             1         \r\nBenchmark duration (s):                  33.69     \r\nTotal input tokens:                      81920     \r\nTotal generated tokens:                  4385      \r\nRequest throughput (req/s):              0.30      \r\nOutput token throughput (tok/s):         130.14    \r\nPeak output token throughput (tok/s):    65.00     \r\nPeak concurrent requests:                2.00      \r\nTotal token throughput (tok/s):          2561.38   \r\n--------------------Time to First Token---------------------\r\nMean TTFT (ms):                          592.15    \r\nMedian TTFT (ms):                        591.43    \r\nP99 TTFT (ms):                           603.63    \r\nP90 TTFT (ms):                           593.99    \r\n----------Time per Output Token (excl. 1st token)-----------\r\nMean TPOT (ms):                          6.53      \r\nMedian TPOT (ms):                        6.43      \r\nP99 TPOT (ms):                           7.75      \r\nP90 TPOT (ms):                           6.89      \r\n--------------------Inter-token Latency---------------------\r\nMean ITL (ms):                           15.55     \r\nMedian ITL (ms):                         15.44     \r\nP99 ITL (ms):                            25.05     \r\nP90 ITL (ms):                            15.67     \r\n---------------------End-to-end Latency---------------------\r\nMean E2EL (ms):                          3369.39   \r\nMedian E2EL (ms):                        3154.05   \r\nP99 E2EL (ms):                           6512.02   \r\nP90 E2EL (ms):                           5079.81   \r\n---------------Speculative Decoding---------------\r\nAcceptance rate (%):                     73.34     \r\nAcceptance length:                       2.47      \r\nDrafts:                                  1776      \r\nDraft tokens:                            3552      \r\nAccepted tokens:                         2605      \r\nPer-position acceptance (%):\r\n  Position 0:                            88.29     \r\n  Position 1:                            58.39     \r\n============================================================\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n<details>\r\n<summary> Essential Elements of an Effective PR Description Checklist </summary>\r\n\r\n- [x] The purpose of the PR, such as \"Fix some issue (link existing issues this PR will resolve)\".\r\n- [x] The test plan, such as providing test command.\r\n- [x] The test results, such as pasting the results comparison before and after, or e2e results\r\n- [ ] (Optional) The necessary documentation update, such as updating `supported_models.md` and `examples` for a new model.\r\n</details>\r\n\r\n",
